# Styling Conventions

## CSS Custom Properties (use these, never hardcode colors)
```
--bg-app, --bg-sidebar, --bg-surface, --bg-elevated
--text-primary, --text-secondary, --text-tertiary
--border-subtle, --border-default, --border-strong
--accent, --accent-soft, --success, --warning, --danger
```

### Opacity / transparency gotcha
`--bg-elevated` is `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` in dark mode â€” nearly transparent.  
**Never use it as a dropdown, popover, or modal background** â€” content behind will bleed through.  
Use `--bg-sidebar` (solid `#080b14` dark / `#ffffff` light) for any floating surface that must be opaque.

## Floating Surfaces (dropdowns, popovers, tooltips)
Use this exact pattern â€” **do not use `position: absolute`** for any floating UI:

```tsx
import { createPortal } from 'react-dom'

// Inside component: capture trigger position when opening
const r = btnRef.current.getBoundingClientRect()
setDropPos({ top: r.bottom + 6, left: r.left })

// Render at document.body to bypass overflow:hidden and stacking contexts
{isOpen && createPortal(
  <div style={{
    position: 'fixed', top: dropPos.top, left: dropPos.left, zIndex: 9999,
    background: 'var(--bg-sidebar)',          // opaque â€” never --bg-elevated
    border: '1px solid var(--border-strong)',
    borderRadius: 10,
    boxShadow: '0 16px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.55), 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.06) inset',
  }}>
    {/* options */}
  </div>,
  document.body
)}
```

**Why:** `.main { overflow-x: hidden }` creates a scroll container that clips `position: absolute` children. `.dashboard { animation: fadeIn }` creates a temporary CSS stacking context. Portals with `position: fixed` bypass both.

Close-on-outside-click must check BOTH the trigger ref AND the portal ref:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (!isOpen) return
  const handler = (e: MouseEvent) => {
    const t = e.target as Node
    if (!btnRef.current?.contains(t) && !dropRef.current?.contains(t)) close()
  }
  document.addEventListener('mousedown', handler)
  return () => document.removeEventListener('mousedown', handler)
}, [isOpen])
```

CSS classes for dropdown options: `filter-option` (hover state defined in index.css).

## Utility Class Naming (defined in index.css)
| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `kpi` | KPI metric card |
| `kpi-label`, `kpi-value`, `kpi-delta` | KPI sub-elements |
| `panel` | Content card / section |
| `panel-title` | Panel heading |
| `panel-action` | Inline link action |
| `grid grid-4` | 4-column responsive grid |
| `grid grid-asym-2` | Asymmetric 2-column (chart + sidebar) |
| `dashboard` | Page wrapper |
| `dash-header`, `dash-title`, `dash-subtitle` | Page header |
| `tbl` | Styled table |
| `badge badge-danger/warning/neutral` | Status badges |
| `dot dot-success/warning/danger` | Status indicator dots |
| `mono` | Monospace text span |
| `burn-grid`, `burn-bar`, `burn-fill` | SLO burn rate bars |
| `dep-row` | Dependency row |
| `filter-row` | Flex row wrapping filter pills |
| `filter-pill` | Clickable filter trigger button (use `<button>`, not `<span>`) |
| `filter-pill active` | Active/selected filter pill state |
| `filter-option` | Option button inside a filter dropdown (applies hover bg) |

## Tailwind
Tailwind v4 is available but used sparingly â€” only for layout utilities not covered by the CSS class system above.  
Do NOT use Tailwind for colors or typography; use CSS variables and the existing class system.

## Fonts
- Body/UI: `IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif`
- Monospace/numbers: `IBM Plex Mono, monospace` (class `mono` or inline `fontFamily`)
